<div class="body" id="fhbody-174636604">
	
		
	

	
		
		<div id="text-174636604" class="p">
			
		 	
				Delta Air Lines CEO Ed Bastian said <a href="https://it.slashdot.org/story/24/07/19/0943232/global-it-outage-linked-to-crowdstrike-update-disrupts-businesses">the massive IT outage</a> earlier this month that stranded thousands of customers <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2024/07/31/delta-ceo-crowdstrike-microsoft-outage-cost-the-airline-500-million.html">will cost it $500 million</a>. From a report:<i> Bastian said the figure is representative of not just the lost revenue, but "the tens of millions of dollars per day in compensation and hotels" over a period of five days. The airline canceled more than 4,000 flights in the wake of the outage, which was caused by a botched CrowdStrike software update and took thousands of Microsoft systems around the world offline. The company had to manually reset 40,000 servers, Bastian said.</i> <b>Further reading</b>: <a href="https://news.slashdot.org/story/24/07/30/033210/delta-seeks-damages-from-crowdstrike-microsoft-after-outage">Delta Seeks Damages From CrowdStrike, Microsoft After Outage</a>.<br>
		 	
		</div>

		

		

		
			
		
	</div>
